==English==
=== Etymology ===
From [[stop the presses]], U.S. newspaper printing [[jargon]].

=== Noun ===
'''stop press''' (''plural'' '''stop press''')
# (''jargon'') The [[event]] or [[news article]] important enough to delay or interrupt the print, or require a reprint, of a [[newspaper]] [[edition]].

=== Interjection ===
'''Stop press!'''
# (''jargon'') Used to announce an event or news article important enough to delay or interrupt the print, or require a reprint, of a [[newspaper]] [[edition]].
# {{idiom}} Used to grab attention, implying importance, news-worthiness, etc.

